      "Type": "Primary_Title",
      "Content": "Personality"
    },
    {
      "Type": "Paragraph",
      "Content": "Ryo is known as a blunt and brazen kid in town. He doesn't hesitate on calling out someone's bullshit regardless of their authority and position."
    },
    {
      "Type": "Bulleted_List",
      "Header": "Tough and protective",
      "Content": "Ryo has a serious and aggressive demeanor, usually scowling or scoffing whenever he's in a conversation.\nHis aggressive personality is usually for a good cause, such as being angry at someone for risking their safety."
    },
    {
      "Type": "Bulleted_List",
      "Header": "Delinquent streak",
      "Content": "His rebellious personality, bordering on delinquency, often shows whenever he gets involved in fights he may or may not have started by himself.\nHe doesn't pick fights without a reason and would often drop out of a fight after hearing a senseless cause of the brawl."
    },
    {
      "Type": "Bulleted_List",
      "Header": "Loyal and empathetic",
      "Content": "Seen as the town's protector, Ryo is aggressively and fiercely loyal to those he considers as part of Pook-Tulay.\nHis loyalty pushes him to go to great lengths in order to help, support, or protect those he considers a part of their community.\nDespite his tough exterior, he is known to silently express empathy towards those around him, particularly those who experienced a troubled past similar to his own."
    },
    {
      "Type": "Primary_Title",
      "Content": "Abilities"
    },
    {
      "Type": "Secondary_Title",
      "Content": "Street combat skills"
    },
    {
      "Type": "Paragraph",
      "Content": "Ryo's main ability is his proficiency in street fighting, particularly hand-to-hand combat. After years of protecting the town, his ability to predict his enemies' moves and adapt to his surroundings are useful in guaranteeing his wins even against adversaries bigger than him in number and size."
    },
    {
      "Type": "Bulleted_List",
      "Header": "Improvisation",
      "Content": "Ryo is known to use the objects around him to his advantage. His violent tendencies during brawls and fights ensure that even the most mundane and unexpected objects around him are turned into deadly weapons at his disposal.\nGossips around Pook-Tulay say that Ryo once used a marble to knock out a mafia boss attempting to take over the town."
    },
    {
      "Type": "Bulleted_List",
      "Header": "Endurance and resilience",
      "Content": "Thanks to his frequent involvement in fights, he had developed a high tolerance for physical pain and maintain stamina even after hours into the fight.\nAnother of Pook-Tulay's gossips around him say that he 'refused to die' from the same mafia boss earlier, and even mocked him after being beaten by his men."
    },
    {
      "Type": "Secondary_Title",
